hose all vertices, except possibly from\none, have degree at most $k$. Our structural result is approximately tight in\nthe sense that graphs generated by this construction always have\nedge-admissibility at most $2k-1$. Our proofs are based on a precise structural\ncharacterization of the graphs that do not contain $\\theta_{r}$ as an\nimmersion, where $\\theta_{r}$ is the graph on two vertices and $r$ parallel\nedges.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Sep 2020 15:04:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-09"}
